INTERVIEW QUESTIONS + ANSWERS
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is the meaning of 755 permission?

Answer:

Owner: read, write, execute (7)

Group: read, execute (5)

Others: read, execute (5)
Common for web directories.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between chmod and chown?

chmod changes permissions

chown changes owner and group

3Ô∏è‚É£ What are ACLs and why are they used?

ACL = Access Control List
Used when default owner/group permissions are not enough.
Provides fine-grained access for multiple users.

4Ô∏è‚É£ What is the sticky bit?

Used on shared directories like /tmp.

Only file owner can delete their file.

Set sticky bit:
chmod +t /sharedfolder

5Ô∏è‚É£ What does SGID do on a directory?

Files created inside the directory inherit group ownership.

chmod 2775 project/

6Ô∏è‚É£ How to check if a file has ACL applied?
getfacl file.txt

7Ô∏è‚É£ What does -rw-r--r-- mean?

Owner: read/write

Group: read

Others: read

8Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference between symbolic and numeric chmod?

Symbolic example:

chmod u+x file


Numeric example:

chmod 755 file

9Ô∏è‚É£ How to restrict a file so only the owner can access it?
chmod 600 file.txt

üîü What command shows extended attributes (immutable)?
lsattr file.txt
